<div tiddler="TaggingMacro" modifier="JeremyRuston" modified="200610051059" created="200512051653" tags="macros">The TaggingMacro produces a list of links to tiddlers that carry the specified tag. If no tag is specified, it looks for tiddlers tagged with the name of the current tiddler. It looks like this:\n{{{\n&lt;&lt;tagging&gt;&gt;\n&lt;&lt;tagging TiddlerTitle&gt;&gt;\n&lt;&lt;tagging sep:[[, ]]&gt;&gt;\n}}}\nIn HTML, the list is formatted like so:\n{{{\n&lt;ul&gt;\n&lt;li class=&quot;listTitle&quot;&gt;List title label&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;tiddlyLink ...&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; onclick=&quot;...&quot;\n	   refresh=&quot;link&quot; tiddlyLink=&quot;ExampleOne&quot;&gt;ExampleOne&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n}}}\nThe optional {{{sep}}} parameter specifies a string of characters to be inserted as a separator between each {{{&lt;li&gt;}}} element. In conjunction with the CSS {{{ul li {display: none;} }}} this allows the tagging list to be formatted as a nicely formatted inline list.</div>